---
import Layout from '../../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Hong Kong Work Visa Insurance Guide 2025 | Employment Visa & Top Talent Pass";
const description = "Complete guide to Hong Kong work visa insurance requirements. Covers Employment Visa, Top Talent Pass Scheme, private health insurance needs, and expat coverage in Hong Kong.";

const tocItems = [
  { id: "overview", label: "Overview" },
  { id: "quick-decision", label: "Is This Right for You?" },
  { id: "official-requirements", label: "Official Requirements" },
  { id: "insurance-requirements", label: "Insurance Requirements" },
  { id: "recommended-providers", label: "Recommended Providers" },
  { id: "costs", label: "Costs Breakdown" },
  { id: "application-timeline", label: "Application Timeline" },
  { id: "scenarios", label: "Real-World Scenarios" },
  { id: "common-mistakes", label: "Common Mistakes" },
  { id: "healthcare-access", label: "Healthcare Access" },
  { id: "faq", label: "FAQs" },
  { id: "verdict", label: "Final Verdict" }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <PageShell
    title="Hong Kong Work Visa Insurance Guide"
    subtitle="Your complete guide to working legally in Hong Kong with proper health coverage"
    heroImage="/images/countries/hong-kong-hero-bg.png"
    tocItems={tocItems}
  >
    <!-- Quick Facts Box -->
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-4">Quick Facts: Hong Kong Work Visa</h3>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm">
        <div><strong>Main Visa Types:</strong> Employment Visa, Top Talent Pass</div>
        <div><strong>Initial Duration:</strong> 2-3 years (renewable)</div>
        <div><strong>Salary Requirement:</strong> Market rate (no fixed minimum)</div>
        <div><strong>Processing Time:</strong> 4-8 weeks</div>
        <div><strong>Health Insurance:</strong> Private (no public access for visa holders)</div>
        <div><strong>PR Pathway:</strong> 7 years continuous residence</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Overview -->
    <section id="overview" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Overview</h2>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        Hong Kong remains one of Asia's premier business hubs, offering a strategic gateway between East and West. The Employment Visa is the standard route for professionals with job offers, while the Top Talent Pass Scheme (TTPS) launched in 2022 attracts high earners and graduates from top universities without requiring a job offer first.
      </p>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        Unlike many developed economies, Hong Kong does not provide public healthcare access to work visa holders. The public Hospital Authority (HA) system is available only to permanent residents and Hong Kong ID holders with specific eligibility. This means private health insurance isn't just recommended—it's essential for any expat worker.
      </p>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        The tax system is famously simple: a flat 15% standard rate or progressive rates up to 17%, with no VAT, no capital gains tax, and territorial taxation (only Hong Kong-sourced income is taxed). Combined with no minimum salary requirements for work visas (just "market rate"), Hong Kong attracts ambitious professionals willing to navigate its competitive environment.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Quick Decision Guide -->
    <section id="quick-decision" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Is a Hong Kong Work Visa Right for You?</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Good Fit If You...</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Have a job offer from a Hong Kong company</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Work in finance, tech, trading, or professional services</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Want low taxes (15% flat rate cap)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Earn HK$2.5M+/year (Top Talent Pass eligible)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Value proximity to mainland China and Asia</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">Consider Alternatives If...</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-amber-800">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>You need affordable public healthcare</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>Housing costs are a major concern (very expensive)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>You prefer work-life balance over career intensity</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>You want citizenship pathway (not available)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>You have concerns about political stability</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Official Requirements -->
    <section id="official-requirements" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Official Requirements</h2>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Visa Categories</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Visa Type", "Duration", "Requirements", "Best For"]}
        rows={[
          ["Employment Visa (GEP)", "2-3 years", "Job offer + employer sponsorship", "Most professionals"],
          ["Top Talent Pass (TTPS) - A", "2 years", "HK$2.5M+ income in past year", "High earners globally"],
          ["Top Talent Pass (TTPS) - B", "2 years", "Top 100 university degree + 3yr experience", "Elite university graduates"],
          ["Top Talent Pass (TTPS) - C", "2 years", "Top 100 university degree, <3yr experience", "Recent elite graduates (quota)"],
          ["Quality Migrant (QMAS)", "2 years", "Points-based (achievements, age, language)", "Exceptional talent without job"],
          ["Intra-Company Transfer", "2-3 years", "Existing employee of multinational", "Internal transfers"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Employment Visa Requirements</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Requirement", "Details", "Notes"]}
        rows={[
          ["Job Offer", "From Hong Kong registered company", "Contract required"],
          ["Salary", "Market rate for the position", "No fixed minimum"],
          ["Qualifications", "Degree or special skills", "Must match job requirements"],
          ["Employer Sponsorship", "Company submits application", "Proven need for foreign hire"],
          ["No Local Candidate", "Employer must justify", "Position not easily filled locally"],
          ["Clean Record", "No criminal history", "Police clearance may be required"]
        ]}
      />

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-4">
        <p class="text-blue-800 font-medium">Top Talent Pass Advantage</p>
        <p class="text-blue-700 text-sm mt-1">TTPS doesn't require a job offer—you can enter Hong Kong first and then find employment. Category A (HK$2.5M+ earners) and Category B (top university + experience) have no annual quota. Category C (recent graduates) is capped at 10,000 per year.</p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Required Documents</h3>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Valid passport</strong> – At least 6 months validity</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Visa application form (ID 990A)</strong> – Completed and signed</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Employment contract</strong> – Detailing position, salary, benefits</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Employer sponsorship form (ID 990B)</strong> – Company details and justification</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Academic certificates</strong> – Degree, professional qualifications</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Proof of work experience</strong> – Reference letters, employment history</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Company documents</strong> – Business registration, financial proof</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Insurance Requirements -->
    <section id="insurance-requirements" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Insurance Requirements</h2>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6">
        <p class="text-red-800 font-medium">⚠️ No Public Healthcare for Work Visa Holders</p>
        <p class="text-red-700 text-sm mt-1">Hong Kong's public Hospital Authority (HA) system is not accessible to non-permanent residents at subsidized rates. You'll pay full "non-eligible person" rates—often 10-20x higher than residents. Private health insurance is essential, not optional.</p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Healthcare Cost Reality</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Service", "Public (Resident Rate)", "Public (Non-Resident)", "Private Hospital"]}
        rows={[
          ["ER Visit", "HK$180", "HK$1,230", "HK$1,500-5,000"],
          ["Hospital Bed (per day)", "HK$120", "HK$5,100", "HK$3,000-15,000"],
          ["GP Consultation", "N/A (specialist system)", "N/A", "HK$500-1,500"],
          ["Specialist Visit", "HK$135", "HK$1,190", "HK$1,500-3,000"],
          ["Surgery (appendix)", "~HK$50,000", "~HK$200,000", "HK$80,000-200,000"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">What Employers Typically Provide</h3>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        Most Hong Kong employers provide group medical insurance as standard. Coverage varies widely—from basic outpatient + hospitalization to comprehensive plans including dental, maternity, and worldwide coverage. Always review your employer's plan details carefully.
      </p>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Coverage Level", "Typical Benefits", "Gaps to Fill"]}
        rows={[
          ["Basic", "Outpatient HK$300-500/visit, hospitalization HK$500-1,500/day", "Major surgery, private rooms, dental"],
          ["Standard", "80% outpatient, HK$2,000/day hospital, annual cap HK$500K", "Premium hospitals, global coverage"],
          ["Premium", "Full outpatient, private room, HK$1M+ annual", "Possibly dental, maternity waiting periods"]
        ]}
      />

      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
        <p class="text-amber-800 font-medium">Common Employer Plan Gaps</p>
        <ul class="text-amber-700 text-sm mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>• Dental and vision (often excluded or minimal)</li>
          <li>• Maternity (waiting periods of 10-12 months common)</li>
          <li>• Pre-existing conditions (exclusions or waiting periods)</li>
          <li>• Coverage outside Hong Kong (emergency only, if any)</li>
          <li>• Mental health (limited sessions or excluded)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Recommended Providers -->
    <section id="recommended-providers" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-6">
        Even with employer coverage, many expats add supplemental insurance for enhanced benefits, global coverage, or to fill gaps in company plans.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">International Providers</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Provider", "Best For", "HK Network", "Annual Cost", "Key Features"]}
        rows={[
          ["Cigna Global", "Comprehensive coverage", "Excellent", "$3,500-8,000", "Direct billing at all major hospitals"],
          ["BUPA Global", "Mental health needs", "Very good", "$3,200-7,500", "No therapy session limits"],
          ["Allianz Care", "European expats", "Good", "$2,800-6,000", "Strong Asia-Pacific presence"],
          ["Now Health", "Value seekers", "Very good", "$2,000-5,000", "Hong Kong-headquartered"],
          ["Aetna International", "US expats", "Good", "$3,000-7,000", "US network integration"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Local Hong Kong Insurers</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Insurer", "Plan Type", "Annual Cost", "Notes"]}
        rows={[
          ["AIA Hong Kong", "Individual medical", "HK$8,000-25,000", "Largest local insurer"],
          ["HSBC Life", "Comprehensive", "HK$10,000-30,000", "Bank-linked plans"],
          ["Manulife HK", "Flexible plans", "HK$8,000-20,000", "Good for families"],
          ["Prudential HK", "Hospital + surgical", "HK$6,000-18,000", "Budget-friendly options"]
        ]}
      />

      <CTABox
        title="Compare Health Insurance for Hong Kong"
        description="Find the right coverage to supplement your employer plan or as standalone protection."
        buttonText="Compare Plans"
        buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
      />
    </section>

    <!-- Costs Breakdown -->
    <section id="costs" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Costs Breakdown</h2>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Visa & Setup Costs</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Item", "Cost (HKD)", "Cost (USD)", "Notes"]}
        rows={[
          ["Employment Visa fee", "HK$230", "$30", "Immigration Department fee"],
          ["Top Talent Pass fee", "HK$230", "$30", "Same as Employment Visa"],
          ["HKID Card", "HK$0", "$0", "Free, mandatory registration"],
          ["Document authentication", "HK$500-2,000", "$65-260", "If required for degrees"]
        ]}
      />

      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
        <p class="text-green-800 font-medium">Low Visa Costs</p>
        <p class="text-green-700 text-sm mt-1">Hong Kong visa fees are remarkably low compared to other destinations. The main costs are employer time for sponsorship and your relocation expenses, not government fees.</p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Mandatory Contributions</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Item", "Employee Contribution", "Employer Contribution", "Notes"]}
        rows={[
          ["MPF (Pension)", "5% of salary", "5% of salary", "Capped at HK$1,500/month each"],
          ["Employees' Compensation", "0%", "0.2-2% of payroll", "Employer's insurance obligation"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Living Costs (Monthly)</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Category", "Hong Kong Island", "Kowloon", "Notes"]}
        rows={[
          ["Rent (1BR)", "HK$18,000-35,000", "HK$14,000-25,000", "Smallest apartments in the world"],
          ["Utilities", "HK$1,000-2,000", "HK$800-1,500", "AC is expensive in summer"],
          ["Transport", "HK$500-1,500", "HK$500-1,500", "MTR + bus, very efficient"],
          ["Food", "HK$5,000-10,000", "HK$4,000-8,000", "Eating out can be cheaper than cooking"],
          ["Health Insurance", "HK$1,500-5,000", "HK$1,500-5,000", "If not fully covered by employer"]
        ]}
      />

      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
        <p class="text-amber-800 font-medium">Housing Reality Check</p>
        <p class="text-amber-700 text-sm mt-1">Hong Kong has some of the world's most expensive housing. A "reasonable" 400 sq ft apartment in a decent area costs HK$20,000-30,000/month. Many expats spend 40-50% of salary on rent. Negotiate housing allowance in your employment package.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Application Timeline -->
    <section id="application-timeline" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Application Timeline</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Week 1-2</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Job Offer & Documentation</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Accept job offer. Gather required documents (passport, degrees, references). Employer prepares company documents and sponsorship form.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Week 2-3</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Application Submission</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Employer submits application to Immigration Department. Can apply online via e-Visa system or in person. Application fee HK$230 paid.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Week 3-8</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Processing</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Immigration reviews application. May request additional documents. Standard processing 4-6 weeks. Large companies with track record often faster.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Week 8-9</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Visa Issuance & Entry</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Receive visa label. Affix to passport at nearest Chinese embassy/consulate (if outside HK) or collect in HK. Enter Hong Kong within 3 months of issuance.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Day 1-30</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">HKID Registration</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Register for Hong Kong Identity Card within 30 days of arrival. Book appointment at Registration of Persons office. HKID required for banking, phone contracts, and daily life.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Real-World Scenarios -->
    <section id="scenarios" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Investment Banker from UK</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">James, 32, joins IB firm in Central. HK$1.5M base + bonus. Employer provides premium Cigna plan. Visa approved in 4 weeks. Shocked by apartment size for HK$28,000/month. 15% tax rate feels amazing after UK.</p>
          <p class="text-green-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Fast approval, excellent coverage, tax savings substantial</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Top Talent Pass - Category A</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Sarah, 35, earned $350K in Singapore last year. Applied for TTPS Category A without job offer. Approved in 3 weeks. Moved to HK, job searched for 2 months, landed tech role. Had to arrange own insurance during job search.</p>
          <p class="text-green-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: TTPS flexibility allowed job hunting from HK</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Tech Startup Employee</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Mike, 28, joins 20-person startup. HK$45,000/month. Basic group insurance only (HK$300/visit cap). Had appendicitis—private hospital bill HK$120,000. Insurance paid HK$35,000. Learned to get supplemental coverage.</p>
          <p class="text-amber-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Basic employer coverage left significant gap</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Teacher at International School</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Lisa, 30, joins prestigious international school. Comprehensive medical + housing provided. Visa sponsored through school's established process. Family-friendly benefits including dependent coverage.</p>
          <p class="text-green-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: International schools often have best expat packages</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Small Company Sponsorship Struggle</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Chen, 27, hired by small trading company. Immigration questioned company's need for foreign hire. Required additional justification letters. Process took 10 weeks. Employer almost gave up.</p>
          <p class="text-amber-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Small companies face more scrutiny—be prepared for delays</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Pre-existing Condition Concerns</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Anna, 38, has managed thyroid condition. Employer insurance excluded pre-existing conditions for 12 months. Purchased individual Cigna plan with full underwriting to ensure medication and monitoring covered from day one.</p>
          <p class="text-amber-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Needed individual plan to cover pre-existing condition</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Common Mistakes -->
    <section id="common-mistakes" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">1. Assuming Employer Insurance is Comprehensive</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">Many employer plans have low limits, high copays, or significant exclusions. Review your policy document carefully. Ask specifically about hospital daily limits, annual caps, and exclusions before assuming you're fully covered.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">2. Not Registering for HKID Within 30 Days</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">HKID registration is mandatory within 30 days of arrival. Without HKID, you can't open bank accounts, sign phone contracts, or access many services. Book your appointment immediately upon arrival—slots fill up.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">3. Underestimating Housing Costs</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">Hong Kong housing is extremely expensive. A "decent" 400-500 sq ft apartment in a reasonable area costs HK$20,000-30,000/month. Negotiate housing allowance in your package, or adjust salary expectations significantly upward.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">4. Expecting Public Hospital Access</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">Work visa holders are charged "non-eligible person" rates at public hospitals—often 10-20x resident rates. Don't assume you can use public healthcare affordably. Budget for private care or comprehensive insurance.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">5. Not Tracking the 7-Year PR Timeline</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">Permanent residence requires 7 years of "continuous ordinary residence." Extended periods outside Hong Kong (more than 6 months) can reset your timeline. If PR is your goal, track your absences carefully.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Healthcare Access -->
    <section id="healthcare-access" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Healthcare System Access</h2>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        Hong Kong has both public and private healthcare systems, but as a work visa holder, you'll primarily use private facilities. Public hospitals are excellent but operate a specialist referral system with long wait times—and charge non-residents full rates anyway.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Private Healthcare Landscape</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
